<article doi="10.15252/emmm.202013901"><fig id="41841"><title>.</title><label>Figure 1</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=41841"/><sd-panel panel_id="114056">Primary <sd-pretag id="sdPretag798098586sd" type="cell" role="component">CD4<sup>+</sup></sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1275654157sd" type="cell" role="component">T-cells</sd-pretag> were activated with α-<sd-pretag id="sdPretag898985033sd" parent-gene-tag-id="103" parent-protein-tag-id="90">CD3</sd-pretag>-<sd-pretag id="sdPretag227199319sd" type="geneprod" role="component">CD28</sd-pretag> beads and infected with <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1475939633sd" type="organism" role="component">HIV</sd-pretag>-1<sub>pNL4-3</sub> or mock-infected. Cells were cultured for two weeks post-infection (p.i.) to <sd-pretag id="sdPretag216844557sd" category="assay">model</sd-pretag> different infection stages (days 3-9 p.i., <em>i.e.</em> productive infection; day 14 p.i., <em>i.e.</em> latent infection) and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1827962516sd" type="organism" role="component">subjected</sd-pretag> to microarray (A, B; n=2) or <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1997704652sd" category="assay">RNA-Seq</sd-pretag> (C; n=3) analysis. (A) <sd-pretag id="sdPretag36917158sd" category="assay">Gene set enrichment analysis</sd-pretag> (<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1313498982sd" category="assay">GSEA</sd-pretag>) of the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1351163194sd" parent-tag-id="10">expression</sd-pretag> of the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1470090401sd" type="molecule" role="component">glycolytic</sd-pretag> pathway (<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1389832254sd" type="organism" role="component">HUMAN</sd-pretag>-GLYCOLYSIS) in mock-infected or <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1954757784sd" type="organism" role="component">HIV-1</sd-pretag> infected cells. (B,C) <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1354228448sd" category="assay">Heatmaps</sd-pretag> of the relative <sd-pretag id="sdPretag849650042sd" parent-tag-id="10">expression</sd-pretag> of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag441636539sd" type="molecule" role="component">glycolytic</sd-pretag> enzymes upon <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2098634313sd" type="organism" role="component">HIV-1</sd-pretag> infection. Data are <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1805824515sd" parent-tag-id="10">expressed</sd-pretag> as Log<sub>2</sub> fold change in <sd-pretag id="sdPretag321315082sd" type="organism" role="component">HIV-1</sd-pretag> infected vs mock-infected cells. For microarray data (B) <sd-pretag id="sdPretag422732628sd" parent-tag-id="10">expression</sd-pretag> values of infected and mock-infected cells at different time points were pooled. For <sd-pretag id="sdPretag242193041sd" category="assay">RNA-Seq</sd-pretag> data (C), <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1699482280sd" parent-tag-id="10">expression</sd-pretag> values in infected cells were normalized using the corresponding time point in mock-infected cells. Adjusted p values (q values) to account for multiple <sd-pretag id="sdPretag300561282sd" type="tissue" role="component">testing</sd-pretag> were calculated by Significance Analysis of Microarrays [SAM <a href="https://paperpile.com/c/8ENJdf/OMTnA">(Tusher <em>et al</em>, 2001)</a>] and Deseq2 for <sd-pretag id="sdPretag150457663sd" category="assay">RNA-Seq</sd-pretag> data <a href="https://paperpile.com/c/8ENJdf/kGt0n">(Love <em>et al</em>, 2014)</a>. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=114056"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="114057"><sd-tag id="sdTag1" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="scRNA-Seq" ext_ids="BAO_0003027" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="rna-seq method" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">scRNA-Seq</sd-tag> of the <sd-tag id="sdTag22" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="expression" ext_ids="BAO_0002785" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="gene expression assay" ext_tax_ids="