xt="expression" ext_ids="BAO_0002785" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="gene expression assay" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">expression</sd-tag> level of the <sd-tag id="sdTag27" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="organism" role="component" text="HUMAN" ext_ids="9606" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="Homo sapiens" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/taxonomy/">HUMAN</sd-tag>-GLYCOLYSIS pathway in (D) was calculated as the average <sd-tag id="sdTag28" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="expression" ext_ids="BAO_0002785" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="gene expression assay" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">expression</sd-tag> of genes comprising the gene list; <sd-tag id="sdTag106" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="expression" ext_ids="BAO_0002785" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="gene expression assay" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">expression</sd-tag> levels in cluster 1 and 2 were compared using Wilcoxon rank sum test. For panels (E, F), significance of <em><sd-tag id="sdTag30" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="gene" role="assayed" text="GPI" ext_ids="2821" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="GPI" ext_tax_ids="9606" ext_tax_names="Homo sapiens" ext_urls="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/">GPI</sd-tag></em> differential <sd-tag id="sdTag107" source="sdapi" category="assay" entity_type="None" role="None" text="expression" ext_ids="BAO_0002785" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="gene expression assay" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="https://bioportal.bioontology.org/ontologies/BAO/?p=classes&amp;conceptid=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioassayontology.org%2Fbao%23">expression</sd-tag> level between clusters (E) or between control and <sd-tag id="sdTag32" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="experiment" text="Env" ext_ids="P04578" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="env" ext_tax_ids="11706" ext_tax_names="HIV-1 M:B_HXB2R" ext_urls="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/">Env</sd-tag><sup>+</sup> <sd-tag id="sdTag33" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="experiment" text="Gag" ext_ids="P04591" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="gag" ext_tax_ids="11706" ext_tax_names="HIV-1 M:B_HXB2R" ext_urls="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/">Gag</sd-tag><sup>+</sup> conditions (F) was assessed by the Wilcoxon rank sum test encoded in FindMarkers Seurat R function. ** p&lt; 0.01, *** p&lt; 0.001; *** p&lt; 0.0001. For panels (D,E) n = 1 donor, 43 cells (untreated), <p>90 cells (<sd-tag id="sdTag34" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="molecule" role="intervention" text="SAHA" ext_ids="CHEBI:45716" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="vorinostat" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/chebi/searchId.do?chebiId=">SAHA</sd-tag></p> ), 91 cells (<sd-tag id="sdTag35" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="gene" role="intervention" text="TCR" ext_ids="6955///6957" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="TRA///TRB" ext_tax_ids="9606///9606" ext_tax_names="Homo sapiens///Homo sapiens" ext_urls="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene////http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/">TCR</sd-tag>), for panel (F) n = 3 donors, 109 cells (control) and 85 cells (<sd-tag id="sdTag36" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="experiment" text="Gag" ext_ids="P04591" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="gag" ext_tax_ids="11706" ext_tax_names="HIV-1 M:B_HXB2R" ext_urls="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/">Gag</sd-tag><sup>+</sup> <sd-tag id="sdTag37" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="protein" role="experiment" text="Env" ext_ids="P04578" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="env" ext_tax_ids="11706" ext_tax_names="HIV-1 M:B_HXB2R" ext_urls="https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/">Env</sd-tag><sup>+</sup>). <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=114057"/></sd-panel></fig><fig id="41842"><title>.</title><label>Figure 2</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=41842"/><sd-panel panel_id="114083">Metabolite <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1008964170sd" category="assay">enrichment analysis</sd-pretag> in latently infected cells as compared to their uninfected counterparts (A) and cells reactivated from latency and compared to latently infected cells (B) <sd-pretag id="sdPretag393186654sd" type="cell" role="component">Jurkat T</sd-pretag>-cells cells, as compared to their uninfected counterparts. The top <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1346760645sd" category="assay">enriched</sd-pretag> pathways were ordered according to p values obtained by Q statistics for metabolic datasets performed with Globaltest (MetaboAnalyst) <a href="https://paperpile.com/c/8ENJdf/tREHS">(Xia <em>et al</em>, 2009)</a>. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=114083"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="114084">Heatmaps of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2012477436sd" type="molecule" role="component">glycolytic</sd-pretag> metabolites in latently infected <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1382661441sd" type="cell" role="component">Jurkat T</sd-pretag>-cells as compared to their uninfected counterparts or <sd-pretag id="sdPretag174329848sd" type="cell" role="component">Jurkat T</sd-pretag>-cells with <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2116345685sd" parent-tag-id="8">HIV-1</sd-pretag> reactivated by <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1662665962sd" type="geneprod" role="component">TNF</sd-pretag> as compared to latently infected cells. Data are displayed as Log<sub>2</sub> fold change <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1323337479sd" parent